Description: Here is a vintage 1965 Gibson SG Special which i bought at a guitar show years ago. It has been modified to use humbuckers and has a pair of early 70s dearmond HBs installed they really sound fantantic also there is a coil tap for the bridge pickup. The back control cover has been made by a previous owner and ive never picked up a new one. The tuners have been replaced with vintage schaller machines and there is some cracking from the tuners screw holes but not shown any signs of becoming a problem Nothing wrong with this instrument that affects playability it is a real rare beauty and sounds fantastic There is a beautiful piece of wood behind the tailpiece that is very well done I assume made to cover the spot where the original vibrato was. Instead of a bridge/tailpiece the instrument has an adjustable wraparound LEO QUAN BadAss bridge. due to the modifications i am pricing this to sell fast so act quickly. Shipping to US only will be packed well in included hardshell case. thnx and enjoy! Price has been lowered to sell now take advantage of the buy now
